Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.03,0:02:05.66,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you to go get the \Ncorruption for me, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.08,0:02:08.31,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,You have that much trouble \Nwith a simple errand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.51,0:02:11.17,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,Well, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.17,0:02:14.28,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,I did get to have a glimpse of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.61,0:02:18.32,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want your apprentice \Nto be turned into an ingredient,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.32,0:02:19.82,Default,Witch,0000,0000,0000,,don't mess up next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.44,0:02:31.98,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,Master, why do you listen to that psycho?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.48,0:02:33.95,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,He took your arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.94,0:02:39.61,Default,Scars,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to concern yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.61,0:02:42.02,Default,Scars,0000,0000,0000,,A master protects his apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.83,0:02:43.97,Default,Scars,0000,0000,0000,,Have faith in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.97,0:02:45.08,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.40,0:02:46.69,Default,Scars,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.69,0:02:48.08,Default,Scars,0000,0000,0000,,I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.83,0:02:55.67,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't I supposed to protect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:14.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,One mandrake petal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.56,0:03:20.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.56,0:03:28.13,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sound, sound through the night forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.13,0:03:31.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sing, sing, young hawthorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.07,0:03:35.98,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Let your thorns pierce the creeping hooves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.69,0:03:44.40,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:48.98,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,When do you think you can finish the order \Nfor the old lady at the foot of the hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.98,0:03:55.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I just finished mixing a pint of hops and five \Nleaves of lavender for the insomnia pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:58.80,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,And this is an enchanted potion \Nfor warding off nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:01.89,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:12.98,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,You used too much magic.\NIt's turned into a sleeping potion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:15.65,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Work a little harder on the proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:16.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.23,0:04:22.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.82,0:04:28.45,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Since I learned of his goal, \NElias seems to have decided
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:31.79,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,to begin seriously teaching me magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.98,0:04:39.62,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What has an effect on what, what needs to be \Nhelped along, and what needs to be avoided...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.35,0:04:44.25,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Strange traditions from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.00,0:04:48.22,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Things that can be both \Nmedicinal and poisonous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:56.79,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wooly bugs, aethonic...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.02,0:05:00.37,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, we're going out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:02.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:10.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A black dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:12.02,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.50,0:05:14.98,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Also known as a church grim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.61,0:05:18.56,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,An excellent watchdog who protects \Nthe church and the graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:21.32,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,One seems to have made himself \Nat home at a nearby church.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:26.62,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Our task is to see if he's hostile or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.18,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There are hostile ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:32.80,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,They're fine so long as \Nyou don't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.23,0:05:34.34,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Usually.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:36.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Usually?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:38.51,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,This is the third one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:40.14,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Their last request.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:44.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why does the church, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:48.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why do they ask you to do things?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.46,0:05:53.40,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I made a mistake a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:55.53,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,They've had an eye on me ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:05:58.54,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like dealing with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:02.75,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,so I take care of some of their business \Nin exchange for their leaving me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.39,0:06:10.47,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that man \Ncalled Elias by a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:13.70,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Pilum Murialis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:17.74,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much I don't know about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:20.13,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.13,0:06:21.16,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:27.19,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I'd asked Angelica to make this for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:32.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:39.77,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,You know why Sleigh Beggies \Nare short-lived, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:46.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,We're frail despite our strong ability \Nto create and soak up magic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.31,0:06:48.12,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.12,0:06:52.10,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,So what you need is a ring to slow \Ndown your production of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:56.09,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,However, the ring can only do so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.48,0:07:00.95,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Become excited, and it'll function more \Nactively, just as your body does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:04.54,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,So, stay as calm as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.42,0:07:06.11,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:08.92,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.92,0:07:11.12,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,As your buyer, I'm responsible for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:13.50,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll look for better solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:16.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:28.04,Magus-Internal/narrator,Angerica,0000,0000,0000,,The right index finger \Nis the guiding finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:31.29,Magus-Internal/narrator,Angerica,0000,0000,0000,,P.S. You're not ready for \Nyour left ring finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.27,0:07:38.85,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias hasn't really said anything \Nabout what happened since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:40.85,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.40,0:07:42.77,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.14,0:07:54.40,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to assign a familiar to you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.40,0:07:55.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:59.79,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,A creature that consumes its \Nmaster's magic, and serves them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.79,0:08:01.57,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,They're useful and loyal,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:03.32,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,and would make great servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.13,0:08:06.34,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Like the one at Angie-san's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.61,0:08:10.99,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,They get to be more familiar with their \Nmasters than the masters themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:15.08,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,They'd be perfect for supporting \Nsomeone as quiet as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.57,0:08:17.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.46,0:08:19.84,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Look, we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:22.46,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,That's the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.54,0:08:34.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.83,0:08:38.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.53,0:08:44.00,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,This could be a bit complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.61,0:08:46.53,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,We may need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.19,0:08:49.98,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go talk to the ones in charge here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.37,0:08:53.21,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Go take a look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.78,0:08:55.91,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if you find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.49,0:08:58.05,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Don't put yourself in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.54,0:08:59.38,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.05,0:09:01.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,All right, get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.79,0:09:03.67,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,This is awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.67,0:09:06.11,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,They're bitten and scratched all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:08.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Were there ever any wild dogs around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:09.56,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:10.63,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:11.90,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:34.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There's something bad growing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.45,0:09:40.37,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.48,0:09:44.52,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:45.53,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:47.27,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of the bad ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.53,0:09:47.27,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:48.21,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.21,0:09:50.39,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer its question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:50.37,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.23,0:09:53.76,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Who does the seamless shirt go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:56.90,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Answer even one thing, and it'll take me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:09:58.87,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I have to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:03.65,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'd let my guard down because \NElias was with me these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.65,0:10:05.27,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:06.17,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.17,0:10:07.19,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.19,0:10:07.94,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.02,0:10:08.83,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.88,0:10:10.04,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:10.86,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:12.50,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to? Where from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:15.02,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.22,0:10:16.71,Default,Anonymous Noface,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.46,0:10:24.23,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Get lost, scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.97,0:10:37.48,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This person... isn't human.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:42.12,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,It's not safe here right now for \Nsomeone as sensitive as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.23,0:10:44.41,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:46.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:47.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.36,0:10:49.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.44,0:11:03.84,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,These cuts...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.42,0:11:06.53,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:08.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:11.02,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I treat him with \Nwhat medicine I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:16.91,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,You remind me of Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.50,0:11:19.60,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.16,0:11:21.02,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.59,0:11:24.38,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Your wounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.57,0:11:31.84,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:33.44,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.86,0:11:35.32,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:47.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The black dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.72,0:12:08.93,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:10.41,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:12.38,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.15,0:12:14.21,Default,Java fern,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:16.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.62,0:12:18.30,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.30,0:12:22.47,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're way too hurt to move, even for a fairy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.86,0:13:07.89,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Bite wounds and shred marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:11.31,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot like that corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.64,0:13:14.06,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't him who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:14.74,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:17.02,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over that dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.77,0:13:22.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:25.42,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any business with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.03,0:13:29.31,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over the dog. That's all I ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.31,0:13:30.84,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a problem for you, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.84,0:13:33.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He helped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:35.75,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you have a proper reason, I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:38.96,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Just hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:40.52,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I need to take him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.53,0:13:44.02,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell did you—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.29,0:13:54.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I messed this one up, but it might \Nactually be useful against humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:13:58.23,Magus-Flashback-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Ulysse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.15,0:14:00.28,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Ulysse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.67,0:14:04.56,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.07,0:14:12.26,Magus-Flashback,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Isabelle? Did they make \Nfun of you for being a redhead again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.63,0:14:15.04,Magus-Flashback,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,It's such beautiful, sunset-colored hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:21.51,Magus-Flashback,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love you no matter \Nwhat color your hair was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.75,0:14:31.88,Magus-Flashback,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.50,0:14:46.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.37,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm burning fairy repellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.20,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The weird ones will leave us alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.49,0:14:53.55,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:56.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,In a forest nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:14:59.79,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are your wounds okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.79,0:15:01.95,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I put medicine on them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.31,0:15:07.34,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,You resemble my younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.95,0:15:09.16,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:10.75,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:15.58,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,She had sunset-colored hair and \Neyes like spring seedlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.97,0:15:17.71,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,She was about your height.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:23.53,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,If you've lost each other, it's \Ndangerous here, so I'll help find...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.53,0:15:24.48,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.30,0:15:27.11,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,She's sleeping under the dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.87,0:15:30.25,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So she's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.58,0:15:33.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite a strange dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.95,0:15:34.79,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:42.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle and I are both human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.85,0:15:48.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'd watched over her ever \Nsince she was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.14,0:15:50.27,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Ulysse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.91,0:15:51.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Always.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.42,0:15:56.59,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought she would \Ncall me with that voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:16:02.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I've met someone like you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:09.08,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Were they able to be with the one they love?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.17,0:16:12.20,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You could say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.47,0:16:14.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But you could say otherwise, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:16.23,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.30,0:16:19.37,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you get those wounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:20.90,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.68,0:16:26.19,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.70,0:16:30.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad the medicine \Ndoesn't last very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:35.34,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you think—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.59,0:16:39.92,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Alice-san, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.25,0:16:43.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You scared me a bit, so I took \Nthe liberty of tying your wrists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.05,0:16:50.69,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.86,0:17:04.96,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going to do anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:08.25,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I have no reason to do anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.66,0:17:10.67,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:12.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask you a question, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.58,0:17:14.74,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.19,0:17:18.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on your reason, \NI may be able to let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.96,0:17:26.09,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I need him as raw material to make a chimera.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.68,0:17:27.65,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Material?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.05,0:17:29.67,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what a chimera is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.57,0:17:35.00,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,They're creatures made by combining \Ntwo creatures using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.00,0:17:40.11,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Some weird brat came to us asking \Nto help find the materials for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:44.65,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Master refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.53,0:17:47.46,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,But there was nothing he could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:50.87,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what happens to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.93,0:17:56.87,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You love him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.87,0:17:57.47,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.99,0:18:04.93,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing good's ever happened \Nto me since I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.16,0:18:11.03,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,But I had a bit of talent, \Nso Master took me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.25,0:18:13.70,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,You're the same way, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:22.42,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not very smart, but I would\N do anything for Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:28.26,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what I think of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.26,0:18:32.14,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He has ulterior motives, but he's kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.51,0:18:34.62,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He's important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.25,0:18:39.22,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,And ultimately, I couldn't \Ngo on if he kicked me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:42.76,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.76,0:18:43.84,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I gave you my reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.84,0:18:45.22,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Now let me go, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.49,0:18:52.88,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,I see what's going on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.63,0:18:56.07,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,You were hiding him from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:18:57.01,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:18:59.10,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Is Renfred nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.10,0:19:01.19,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I came out here by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:01.85,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Master is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:05.84,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:09.06,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you guys here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:11.36,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,To inspect that there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.35,0:19:14.90,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,A mage? Inspect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:15.82,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.04,0:19:20.57,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,It's only recently that he \Nawoke as a black dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:23.97,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,That thing won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.97,0:19:25.07,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}thing{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.07,0:19:25.90,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:27.22,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.22,0:19:31.91,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, there's some \Ncreepy kid threatening us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:34.35,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He took Master's arm as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.89,0:19:37.15,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.39,0:19:39.59,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.59,0:19:41.39,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Do something about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.77,0:19:43.59,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,How does that benefit us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.59,0:19:46.83,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He's already got chimeras \Nwandering around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.28,0:19:51.43,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse up front and the dog's \Nwounds are both his chimera's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:56.36,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Concern yourself with the dog, and \Nyour kitten will be in danger, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:00.95,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Was that not a good enough reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:03.82,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.60,0:20:07.32,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,Why the flimsy voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.32,0:20:11.89,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't think you'd \Nbe so quick to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.32,0:20:16.86,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,If he's left running around, the church will\Ncome complaining to me later, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:20.66,Default,Diablo,0000,0000,0000,,So what does this "kid" look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:24.17,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.17,0:20:28.65,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He looks like a kid, but I see \Nall kinds of things overlapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:30.57,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He's, like, blurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.32,0:20:33.03,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He has this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.10,0:20:33.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.13,0:20:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...creepy grin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.35,0:20:38.82,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,What are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.35,0:21:00.68,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,Renfred's puppy is so poorly trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.18,0:21:03.44,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,She spilled everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.04,0:21:04.86,Default,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:05.99,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.50,0:21:08.13,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,Did I get the wrong one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.85,0:21:12.74,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, what does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:16.14,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,That girl's just a guinea pig, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.63,0:21:20.62,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you'd become \Nattached to a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.58,0:21:25.38,Default,Sophie,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Pilum Murialis?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.18,0:21:42.33,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Master said he's a mage \Nfrom a fantasy story.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.82,0:21:49.94,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,At times, he lends a hand, and \Nat times, he shows his fangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.89,0:21:58.05,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,Something incomplete that tries\Nto pretend to be human, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.67,0:22:00.63,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.26,0:22:03.72,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,He's not that half-assed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.67,0:22:08.63,Magus-Internal/narrator,Track jacket,0000,0000,0000,,This thing could never become human.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.00,0:23:58.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The mage becomes a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.27,0:24:03.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Having lost himself to rage, \Nhe shows his beastly instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.67,0:24:07.37,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The wounded girl comes to a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.75,0:24:08.82,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
